                            <comment id="410193" author="eaujames" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2024 17:27:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a 2.12.9 with the &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14339&quot; title=&quot;Add a option %H to avoid the jobid too long&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14339&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14339&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; obdclass: add option %H for jobid &quot; backported.&lt;br/&gt;
These errors and corrupted jobid are only seen when using &quot;%H&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The race seems to be in &quot;lli_jobid&quot;, the field is not protected and have concurrent accesses (read/write) for buffer IOs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-c&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; jobid_interpret_string(
....
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;H&apos;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;short&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt; hostname. Cut at first dot */&lt;/span&gt;           
        l = snprintf(jobid, joblen, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&quot;%s&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,                  
                     init_utsname()-&amp;gt;nodename);            
        p = strnchr(jobid, joblen, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;.&apos;&lt;/span&gt;);                   
        if (p) {                                           
                *p = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote-red&quot;&gt;&apos;\0&apos;&lt;/span&gt;;                                 
                l = p - jobid;                             
        }                                                  
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;break&lt;/span&gt;;                                             
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think that backporting  the &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16251&quot; title=&quot;Fill jobid in an atomic way&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16251&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16251&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; obdclass: fill jobid in a safe way&quot; (&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/48915&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/48915&lt;/a&gt;) should fix the issue.&lt;br/&gt;
But races are still possible with lli_uid/lli_gid/lli_jobid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="410181" author="adilger" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2024 17:01:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In particular, the &quot;invalid jobid size&quot; error was fixed on master long ago, not sure if those fixes were backported to b2_15 or not. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="410179" author="adilger" created="Fri, 5 Apr 2024 16:59:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You don&apos;t mention what Lustre version is running anywhere in the ticket. There definitely have been fixes in jobid handling, mostly by Feng Lei,  so this may already be fixed. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
